{"/service/ndnp/txdn/batch_txdn_kestrel_ver01/data/sn85060004/00516994733/1937091201/0411.xml":{"full_text":"2\nPART SEVEN.\n\u2018Announcements\nImproved Scenic Coast to Coast Highway Attracts Motorists From All Sections of Nation!\n1\nRoswell Hotel, Del Rio Texas i\nLeading Hotel On\nHighway 90 Between\nSan Antonio and El Paso.\n\u2014\u2014100 ROOMS\u2014 g\nAll With Bath and Ceiling Fans i\nF. L. CHILDS, Manager\nHome of\nPETERSEN COMPANY i\n\u201cA Little of Everything\u201d s\nBRACKETTVILLE, TEXAS\nGroceries\u2014Dry Goods\u2014Hardware\nWindmills and Engines\u2014Lumber and Building Supplies\nB e e e St Yt et e e e S B et et ettt\nPicture shows entrance to\nCAMP JUDGE ROY BEAN, LANGTRY, TEXAS\nNamed after the old place of Judge Roy Bean, \u201cLaw West of the Pecos.\u201d 3\nWe operate a modern tourist camp and cafe, Located one mile from the\nMexican border and on the Coast-to-Coast Highway. E. R. SKILES, Prop.\nB R\nInterior view of the\nKERR HOTEL Al\\iD COFFEE SHOP i\n24.-Hour Bervice\u2014Nationally Known z\nSANDEREON, TEXAS J. W. DOWNUM, Mgr.\net 5 et b e S e e e e e e B e e e S e e S e e\nOm,(.;......rmm,mmm.m S\nl JOE KERR\u2014SANDERSOH, TEXAS\nBanker\u2014Merchant\u2014Rancher\nThis is part of the twe;lty-sl)_z_ cars of lambs\nshipped from Sanderson by i\nIRA DEATON, SANDERSON, TEXAS i\nWANT ADS\u2014FANNIN 1231\nAnnouncements\nRoad Via Brackettville, Del Rio, Comstock, Sanderson, Langtry, Alpine and Marfa picturesque and Time-Saving Route,\nPicture shows i\nthe home of 2\nW. H. Dodd\nGeneral i\nMerchandise 1\nOne-half block i\nfrom Judge Roy\nBean's \u2018Law\nWest of the\nPecos\u201d Place,\nLangtry, Texas.\nALSO VISIT\nLangtry\nCourts\nNEW AND s\nMODERN\nOn Highway 90,\nmile from l\nJudge Roy\nBean's Place. X\nLANGTRY,\nTEXAS\nAnnouncements\nProbably nowhere in the state of\nTexas is there more scenic land than\nthat section which lies due west\nfrom San Antonio and west of the\nPecos river, generally referred to as\nthe \"Big Bend country\u201d. With the\nexception of approximately 75 miles\nof road now under construction the\ncoast to coast highway, along the\n_international border, is completed\n.and offers to motorists a direct\nroute with driving hours shortened\nand made more pleasant.\nA state-wide movement is now un\nderway to finance establishment of\na Big Bend national park. Besides\nembracing 788,000 acres in Texas the\nproposed Big Bend park would in\nclude 400,000 acres on the Mexican\nside of the Rio Grande river. Under\nthe plan the park would become the\nBig Bend International Peace park.\nBoundaries have already been es\ntablished and the land has been\nsurveyed for the park. So far Texas\ndoes not have a national park. This\nproject would provide not only a\nwonderful recreation ground for\nTexans but would also attract lead\ning scientists of the nation through\nthe opportunities for research which\nit would afford. Included within the\npark would be an entire mountain\nrange, the Chisos mountains, and\nthe Grand Canyon of the Rio\nGrande river. Altitudes within the\npark would range from 2000 to 12,000\nfeet above sea level, including al\nmost every type of climate, it has\nbeen pointed out.\nProgressive merchants along the\ninternational border route are\ngreatly interested in any movement\nfor the betterment of West Texas\nand have contributed their support\nin popularizing this section.\nALPINE.\nJ. E. Casner, owner of the Casner\nMotor company at Alpine is one of\nthe strong boosters for the Big Bend\nsection. Casner is the local chairman\nof the Big Bend park finance com\nmittee and has been active in or\nganizing committees throughout the\nstate to take over the raising of\nnecessary funds. Casner explains\nthat the plan of the commission is\nto raise the money by popular sub\nscriptions. Individual contributions\nof \u201c$1 or more will be sought\nthroughout the state, he said. Cas\nner is one of Alpine\u2019s most prom\ninent business men. He is Buick and\nChevrolet dealer and handles a full\nline of auto accessories.\nEstablished in 1904 and serving\nits community with a banking ser\nvice second to none, The Firsh Na\ntional Bank of Alpine has been\nSanderson\nBakery\nBakers of\nHigh Quality\nBread and Pastry\nFred Schmidt, Prop.\nSANDERSON, TEXAS\nO 28T R R B R S S s R\nHome of\nSANDERSON MERCANTILE CO.\nSANDERSON, TEXAS\nA. D. BROWN, President J. D. NICHOLS, Secy.-Treas.\n\u201cThe Store of Service and Quality\u201d\nFood for People Feed for Livestock\nPractically Everything for You and Yours\nTelephone 40\n\nm&zs\ufb01:s\ufb01mwwm\ufb01%mmmm\u00bb\ufb01wwmw\u2014_\u2014\u2014\u2014w\u2014\u2014\nome O\nTHE KERR MERCANTILE CO.\nJOE KERR, President JAMES KERR, Vice-Pres,\nGENERAL MERCHANDISE\u2014SANDERSON, TEXAS\nWe Sum\u2019ll% Every Need for the Home\nLumber\u2014Building Material\u2014Windmills\nA\nA Complete\nDrug Store\nService!\nManufacturer of\nRamsey's Fly Repellant\nand\nRamsey's Screw Worm Killer\nRAMSEY\nDRUG STORE\nComstock, Texas\nWANT ADS\u2014FANNIN 1231\nAnmouncements\none of the leaders in'civic move\nments envolving Alpine. Through\nout its 33 years of service the bank\nhas maintained an excellent record.\nIts officers are H. L. Kokernot,\npresident, G. W. Baines, vice-pres\nident, Z. M. \u2018Decie, Vice-president\nand G. B. Crawford, cashier. The\nFirst National Bank of Alpine has\na capital and surplus of $100,000,\nand is a member of the Federal\nDeposit Insurance Corppration.\nBoasting a record of well over\n25 years the Alpine Lumber com\npany is one of best established bus\niness \u2018houses in this section. Build\ning and water supply material, gen\neral hardware, paints and oils, fenc\ning materials, ranch supplies, and in\nfact everything to keep the home\ngoing is included in its stock.\nHoused in a modern building this\ncompany reflects the progressive\nness of its officials, F. E. Gilleit,\npresident, J. W. Gillett, vice-presi\ndent and G. A. Gillett, secretary\n\u201ctreasurer.\nGeorge's Cafe and Beer Parlor\noffers fine food at all hours and is\none of the favorite eating places\nof citizens of Alpine and travelers.\nFoods of every kind are properly\ncooked and served and beer is kept\nat the correct temperature. George\u2019s\nCafe has earned a widespread rep\nutation for \u2018its excellent Mexican\ndishes, prepared as they are in. the\nnative land. The American foeds\nserved here have also proven pop\nular. The management of George\u2019s\nCafe is optimistic over the business\noutlook and predicts improved con\nditions in every field.\nBRACKETTVILLE\n\u201cA Little of Everything\u201d is the\nslogan of Petersen company Of\nBrackettville and has won for this\nfirm a lengthy list of customers. A.\nE. Barthburger is owner and man\nager. Groceries, dry goods, hard\nware, windmills and engines, lum\nber and building supplies, are all\na part of the stock of Petersen\ncompany. For the past 57 years the\nfirm has been in business in Brack\nettville and for the last 10 years\nhas been owned and managed by\nBarthburger.\nCOMSTOCK\nIn Comstock drug needs are cap\nably supplied by the Ramsey Drug\nstore, owned and operatedby Joe\nF. Ramsey for the past 6 years. In\naddition to a complete drug store\nservice Ramsey is also manufac\nturer. of the popular Ramsey Fly\nRepellant and Ramsey Screw Worm\n\u2018Killer. For the past 5 years his store\n\u2018has been distributor for Borden\u2019s\n1products in Comstock.\nDEL RIO.\nThe Brinkley hospital, located in\nthe Roswell hotel, Del Rio, was\nfounded by Dr. John R. Brinkley,\nwho for the past 20 years has spe\ncialized in the treatment of pros-\nWhen visiting in the towns\nmentioned here, patronize\nthe firms on this page who\nhave made this message\npossible.\nI The First\n\ni National Bank\nALPINE, TEXAS\n\nCapital and Surplus $100,000.00\nH. L. KOKERNOT, President\n4. W. BAINES, Vice Pres.\ni Z. M. DECIE, Vice Pres.\nf G. B. CRAWFORD, Cashier\nMember of Federal\nDeposit Insurance Corporation\nAnnouncements\ntate diseases. The magnitude of his\nsuccess can hardly be appreciated\nunless one has the opportunity of\npersonally visiting the Brinkley hos\npital. Dr. Brinkley is president of\nthe Rotary club of Del Rio and is\nvery active in civic and educational\nenterprises, making very liberal con\ntributions along these lines. The\nBrinkley home, with its fine gard\nens, flowers, shrubbery and colorful\nfountains, is indeed a show place\nof Del Rio\nThe Citizens Bridge company, of\nwhich F. N. Garcia is president,\nowns and operates what is said to\nbe the longest bridge spaning the\nRip Grande. The management of\nthe Citizens Bridge company wel\ncomes everyone to old Mexico over\nthis new, modern route.\nOne of the leading hotels on\nUnited States Highway 90, between\nSan Antonio and El Paso is the\nRoswell hotel at Del Rio. This mod-~\nern hostelry boasts 100 rooms, all\nwith bath and ceiling fans. F. L.\nChilds, manager, is well known\nthroughout the country and is one\nof the most popular hotel managers\nin this section.\nLANGTRY.\nW. H. Dodd\u2019s store, just one-half\nblock from Judge Roy Bean\u2019s \u201cLaw\nWest of the Pecos\u201d place in Lang\ntry, is a popular gathering place\nand shopping center for citizens of\nthe community. The store-features\na line of general merchandise.\nIn Langtry, on United States\nHighway 90 about three-fourths of\na mile from Judge Roy Bean's place\nis the Langtry Courts. These tour\nist cottages are new and modern\nthroughout and are comfortably\nfurnished. The management ex\ntends a warm welcome to travelers.\nLocated on the Coast-to-Coast\nhighway and just one mile from\nthe Mexican border is the Camp\nJudge Roy Bean, named for the\nfamous Judge Roy Bean's place,\n\u201cLaw West of the Pecos.\u201d The camp\nis modern and offers every conven\nience to tourists. Quarters are clean\nand neatly equipped and the cafe\nfacilities are available. In addition\nthe tourist is provided with gas and\noil service and attendants familiar\nwith this section of the country are\non duty at all times to furnish cor\nrect road information. E. R. Skiles,\none of Langtry\u2019s most progressive\nbusiness men, is proprietor.\nMARFA.\nTen thousand Hereford bulls\u2018\nraised and sold from his ranch in\n10 years, that is the record of Luke\nBrite with his well-watered Rim\nrock ranch that lies southeast of\nMarfa 30 to 40 miles, and south\nof Valentine. It is believed to stand\no The Lon;zest Bridge \u201cSpannlng the Rio Gran\ufb01e\nOWNED AND OPERATED BY\nCitizens Bridge Company g\nDEL RIO, TEXAS\nF. N. GARCIA, President\nWelcomes everyone to Mexico. The liveliest spot\non the Border for the Whole Famiiy.\ne ettt b e A e e e et\n\u2018We Invite Your Inspection. Be at Home at\nCAMP SANDERSON\u2014SANDERSON, TEXAS\nAll\"\u201d Modern\u2014Steam Heat-\u2014Connecting Showers\nand Garages. Service, Comfort and Courtesy\nOur Motto. Rates $1.50\nAcross Bridge East Edge of Town on Highway 90\nMR. AND MRS. R. E. FRED, Owners\ne et e et ettt i i et S il\nGeorge's\nCafe\nand Beer Parlor\nALPINE, TEXAS\nBeer That Is Always\nCold and Fresh\nReal Mexican Dinners\nAll Kinds of\nAmer,lcan Dishes\nTHE SAN ANTONIO LIGHT.\nAnnouncements\nas the all-American record for bulls\nraised and sold by the same man in\nanything like a 10-year period. It\nran approximately 1000 bulls a\nyear for 10 straight years, from\n1910 to 1920. The ranch straddles\nthe great Rimrock wall. On the\nRio Grande side it is broken with\nridges and dusky canyons. On the\nupper side the country is rolling,\nwith little brush, fine grass and an\noccasional herd of antelope. Brite's\nrecord and the 85 miles of water\nline on his ranch testify to an am\nbition realized.\nTourists to Marfa will find the\nYucca Courts comfortable and\nmodern in every respect. These\ncottages have just been completed\nand each is furnished with the\nmost modern equipment available.\nInner-spring mattresses are pro\nvided for each bed, assuring com\nfortable rest. The rates are rea\nsonable and garage space is. pro\nvided with each cottage.\nSANDERSON, I\nSanderson is the mid-point city\nbetween San Antonio and El Paso,\na distance of 592 miles, located on i\nthe Scenic Border highway 90, at\nthe junction of Highway 285. It is\nfast becoming a true cross-road of i\nthe world, as it is also the mid\npoint city from Laredo to the Cav-\nerns of Carlsbad, New Mexico. Pan-\nAmerican travelers find it is the\nlogical stopping point to the north- l\nwest. For the convenience of the\ntraveling public, hotels, tourist i\ncamps, Western Union, service sta\ntion and cafes give 24-hour service. i\nThe postoffice is in the Kerr Hotel\nbuilding and mail sent in care of\nthe hotel can be picked up at all\nhours. \u201cA. A, A.\u201d information can i\nalso be obtained there. i\nSanderson is the train division\nof the Southern Pacific railroad.\nSheep and goat ranching are the I\nmost thriving industries, and ap-\nproximately three million pounds of\nwool and mohair, as well as 150,000\nhead of livestock are shipped to the\nmarket from this point yearly.\nBlack tail deer, blue quail, bob-i\ncats javalina hogs and other wild\ngame make a haven of sport for\nthe hunter. Sanderson, with a\n2800-foot elevation and in the cen-\nter of rugged hills, enjoys cool I\nnights in the summer and balmy\ndays during the winter.\nThe Kerr Hotel and Coffee shop\nis nationally known. Twenty-four\nhour service is rendered. J. W.\nDownum is the manager. i\nThe Kerr Mercantile company of\nSanderson with slightly less than\na quarter of a century of service\nto its record is today the largest\ndepartment store in the Trans-Pe\ncos. It is completely modern and\nis the headquarters for the ranch\n(Continued on Page 3, Col. 1)\ne e e 8 e e e e e e B e R et\nRS mesms\ni\n\ni CASNER\nMOTOR CO.\nf Dealers in America\u2019s Best\ni AUTOMOBILES AND\nACCESSORIES\n\ni ALPINE, TEXAS\ni J. E. CASNER, Owner\ni\nAnnouncements\n1\nBrinkley Hospital\nDEL RIO, TEXAS ;o\ni Located in Roswell Hot\u00e9l\nJNO.